Okay, this is the tricky bit.  We have two types of relation adapters now (for backwards compatibility). We have to try to pass the charm_instance in case it's NEW, but that may fail with a TypeError (unexpected keyword argument).  If the TypeError fails, then we instantiate without the charm_instance= part as it's an OLD adapter.

e.g. re-write the bit above to something like:

    try:
        cls = self._adapters[relation_name]
    except KeyError:
        cls = OpenStackRelationAdapter
    try:
        adapter = cls(relation, charm_instance=self.charm_instance)
    except TypeError:
        adapter = cls(relation)

